    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "I agree with disallowing ``switch`` with only a default case. In fact, I don't understand when and why that would ever have been useful, independently of the introduction of ``if``...\r\n\r\nMaybe there is a separate second question, namely whether to allow switches with only a single non-default case? Those are the ones that can theoretically be replaced by ``if``s. But for those I'd say it's fine to keep allowing them.",
